      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ETERNAL WINE (1) got the job done at Bunbury two back in a CL3 before stepping up in trip on the Scarpside at Pinjarra most recently. She was only 1.7L there but coming back to the short course looks ideal. Should get every chance to bounce back to winning ways in the small field. MANDIBLE MAGIC (2) sat handy and shot away to score by 2.1L over this trip at Ascot last start and turned in a strong figure in the process. She looks ready to go on with the job now with Riordan's 3kg claim coming in handy. Can repeat the dose with further improvement expected third-up. SHE'S CAPITANA (3) comes here off a break but hasn't been sighted publicly. Pike hops back on board today after partnering her throughout her last campaign. She went well fresh last campaign and creates some interest first-up. ARTIE'S ECLIPSE (4) was good in this scenario fresh and won't be far away. RIGATONI (5) rounds out the five.",
